## Quick Reference: Common Calculations

### **Frame Buffer Sizes (at 1080p)**

| Format       | Bytes/Pixel | Size   | Use Case |
|--------------|-------------|--------|----------|
| Grayscale    | 1           | 2 MB   | B&W cameras, ML input |
| Bayer 10-bit | 1.25        | 2.6 MB | Raw sensor data |
| YUV 4:2:0    | 1.5         | 3 MB   | Video encoding (h.264) |
| RGB565       | 2           | 4 MB   | Embedded displays |
| YUV 4:2:2    | 2           | 4 MB   | Professional video |
| RGB888       | 3           | 6 MB   | Full quality processing |
| RGBA         | 4           | 8 MB   | With transparency |

### **Common Resolutions**

| Resolution  | Pixels    | Multiplier vs 1080p |
|-------------|-----------|---------------------|
| VGA         | 640×480   | 0.14× (307K) |
| HD          | 1280×720  | 0.44× (921K) |
| FHD (1080p) | 1920×1080 | 1.00× (2.07M) |
| QHD         | 2560×1440 | 1.78× (3.68M) |
| 4K UHD      | 3840×2160 | 4.00× (8.29M) |
| 8K UHD      | 7680×4320 | 16.00× (33.2M) |

### **Memory Hierarchy (for context)**

| Type | Size | Speed | Use |
|------|------|-------|-----|
| CPU Registers | 32-256 bytes | 1 cycle | Active computation |
| L1 Cache | 32-64 KB | 3-4 cycles | Hot code/data |
| L2 Cache | 256KB-1MB | 10-20 cycles | Recently used |
| L3 Cache | 2-32 MB | 30-70 cycles | Shared data |
| Main RAM | GB range | 100+ cycles | Working set |
| Flash/SSD | GB-TB | 100,000+ cycles | Storage |